description:
The Faith-based and Community Initiatives and Rick Warren's P.E.A.C.E. Plan should be of great concern especially to Seventh-day Adventists, because our understanding of Bible prophecy, Revelation 13:11-17, teaches us that when the Mark of the Beast (Sunday Observance) is enforced, dissenters will not be able to buy or sell and will be persecuted. Now that government-run churches (including all churches with 501 (c)(3) statuses) are rapidly becoming the distributing centers of government resources and services, when Sunday observance is mandated, God's faithful children will not have access to any of the basic necessities of life, unless they receive the Mark of the Beast and renounce the Seventh-day Sabbath. What two choices will the Seventh-day Adventist denomination, which is presently a 501(c)(3) organization (a government-run church) have, once the Mark of the Beast is enforced? What should A.D.R.A and other agencies of the Seventh-day Adventist Church do now, along with its members? Let us watch and pray!

Website: www.prophesyagain.org
